        <details>
          <summary>When does Humana usually make its quarterly dividend announcement?</summary>
          <p>Humana typically announces its quarterly dividend in mid-to-late February, April, July, and October. However, the exact dates can vary slightly from year to year, so investors should monitor the company's investor relations press releases for the official declaration.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>How long after the Humana quarterly dividend announcement is the money paid?</summary>
          <p>The payment date is usually scheduled about four to six weeks after the declaration date. The exact timeline will be specified clearly in the initial dividend announcement press release.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>Does Humana increase its dividend every year?</summary>
          <p>While past performance is not indicative of future results, Humana has a strong historical track record of increasing its dividend payout annually. This consistent growth is a key reason why it is favored by long-term dividend growth investors.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>Why did the Humana stock price drop on the ex-dividend date?</summary>
          <p>This is a normal mechanical adjustment. On the ex-dividend date, the stock begins trading without the value of the upcoming dividend attached to it. Consequently, the exchange specialists automatically adjust the stock price down by the exact amount of the dividend to reflect this outflow of cash from the company.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>Can I automatically reinvest my Humana dividends?</summary>
          <p>Yes, most major brokerage firms offer a Dividend Reinvestment Plan (DRIP) that allows you to automatically use your cash dividends to purchase fractional shares of Humana stock without incurring any additional trading fees.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </section>
